 \int(\cos m\theta) (\cos n\theta)d\theta=0 
 \int_0^{\pi}(\cos m\theta) (\cos n\theta)d\theta=0 
 (\cos m\theta) (\cos n\theta) =  \frac12 \left(\cos((m+n)\theta)+\cos(m-n)\right) 
 \begin{align} \int(\cos m\theta) (\cos n\theta)d\theta &= \int \frac12 \left(\cos((m+n)\theta)+\cos(m-n)\right)d\theta\\ &=\frac12\left(\frac1{m+n}\sin((m+n)\theta) + \frac1{|m-n|}\sin((m-n)\theta)\right) + C \end{align} 
